Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: rockchip-vaapi
Architecture: arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
         libva2,
         librockchip-mpp1
Description: VA-API driver for Rockchip RK3588 via MPP
 Hardware video acceleration driver that bridges the VA-API (libva)
 interface to Rockchip MPP (librockchip-mpp1) for the RK3588/RK3576 SoC.
 .
 Enables H.264 and VP9 hardware decode in applications like Firefox via
 zero-copy DRM PRIME 2 surface export.
 .
 Install LIBVA_DRIVER_NAME=rockchip and point LIBVA_DRIVERS_PATH to
 /usr/lib/aarch64-linux-gnu/dri to use.
